premise_source_doc_sentence: Dominick John Dunne  (  October 29 , 1925 -- August 26 , 2009  )  was an American producer , writer and investigative journalist .

He began his career as a producer in film and television , noted for involvement with the pioneering gay film The Boys in the Band  (  1970  )  and the award winning drug film Panic in Needle Park  (  1971  )  .
He turned to writing in the early 1970s .
After the 1982 murder of his daughter Dominique , he came to focus on the ways in which wealth and high society interacts with the judicial system .
A frequent contributor to Vanity Fair , Dunne also appeared regularly on television discussing crime from the 1980s to the end of his life .
She is the daughter of the actors Griffin Dunne and Carey Lowell , and the granddaughter of the writer and journalist Dominick Dunne .

His portrait of writer Dominick Dunne scribbling in his notebook during his coverage for Vanity Fair of the OJ Simpson trial in Los Angeles was chosen for the cover of Dunne 's best-selling memoir about the trial , `` Another City , Not My Own '' .
Dominick Dunne : After the Party is a 2008 documentary directed by Kirsty de Garis and Timothy Jolley .
A Season in Purgatory is a 1993 novel by Dominick Dunne .
Hollywood outcast , top-selling author and reporter , Dominick Dunne is a prominent columnist and society correspondent .
